-<a name="X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT"></a><div id="X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT-def"><a name="L127"></a><tt class="py-lineno">127</tt> <a class="py-toggle" href="#" id="X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT-toggle" onclick="return toggle('X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT');">-</a><tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-keyword">class</tt> <a class="py-def-name" href="x2go.backends.terminal.stdout.X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT-class.html">X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT</a><tt class="py-op">(</tt><tt class="py-base-class">object</tt><tt class="py-op">)</tt><tt class="py-op">:</tt> </tt>
-</div><div id="X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT-collapsed" style="display:none;" pad="+++" indent="++++"></div><div id="X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT-expanded"><a name="L128"></a><tt class="py-lineno">128</tt>  <tt class="py-line">    <tt class="py-docstring">"""\</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L129"></a><tt class="py-lineno">129</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    Class for managing X2go sessions on a remote X2go server via Paramiko/SSH. </tt> </tt>
-<a name="L130"></a><tt class="py-lineno">130</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    With the L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT} class you can start new X2go sessions, resume suspended </tt> </tt>
-<a name="L131"></a><tt class="py-lineno">131</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    sessions or suspend resp. terminate currently running sessions on a </tt> </tt>
-<a name="L132"></a><tt class="py-lineno">132</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    connected X2go server.</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L133"></a><tt class="py-lineno">133</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
-<a name="L134"></a><tt class="py-lineno">134</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    When suspending or terminating sessions there are two possible ways:</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L135"></a><tt class="py-lineno">135</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
-<a name="L136"></a><tt class="py-lineno">136</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        1. Initialize an X2go session object, start a new session (or resume)</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L137"></a><tt class="py-lineno">137</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        and use the L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT.suspend()} or L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT.terminate()} method</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L138"></a><tt class="py-lineno">138</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        to suspend/terminate the current session object.</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L139"></a><tt class="py-lineno">139</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        2. Alternatively, you can pass a session name to L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT.suspend()}</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L140"></a><tt class="py-lineno">140</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        or L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT.terminate()}. If a session of this name exists on the</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L141"></a><tt class="py-lineno">141</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        X2go server the respective action will be performed on the session.</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L142"></a><tt class="py-lineno">142</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
-<a name="L143"></a><tt class="py-lineno">143</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    An L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT} object uses two main data structure classes: </tt> </tt>
-<a name="L144"></a><tt class="py-lineno">144</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
-<a name="L145"></a><tt class="py-lineno">145</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        - L{X2goSessionParams}: stores all parameters that have been passed to the </tt> </tt>
-<a name="L146"></a><tt class="py-lineno">146</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        constructor method.</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L147"></a><tt class="py-lineno">147</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
-<a name="L148"></a><tt class="py-lineno">148</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        - C{X2goServerSessionInfo} backend class: when starting or resuming a session, an object of this class </tt> </tt>
-<a name="L149"></a><tt class="py-lineno">149</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        will be used to store all information retrieved from the X2go server.</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L150"></a><tt class="py-lineno">150</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
-<a name="L151"></a><tt class="py-lineno">151</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @param geometry: screen geometry of the X2go session. Can be either C{<width>x<height>}</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L152"></a><tt class="py-lineno">152</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        or C{fullscreen}</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L153"></a><tt class="py-lineno">153</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @type geometry: str</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L154"></a><tt class="py-lineno">154</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @param depth: color depth in bits (common values: C{16}, C{24})</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L155"></a><tt class="py-lineno">155</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @type depth: int</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L156"></a><tt class="py-lineno">156</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @param link: network link quality (either one of C{modem}, C{isdn}, C{adsl}, C{wan} or C{lan})</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L157"></a><tt class="py-lineno">157</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @type link: str</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L158"></a><tt class="py-lineno">158</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @param pack: compression method for NX based session proxying</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L159"></a><tt class="py-lineno">159</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @type pack: str</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L160"></a><tt class="py-lineno">160</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @param cache_type: a dummy parameter that is passed to the L{X2goProxyBASE}. In NX Proxy </tt> </tt>
-<a name="L161"></a><tt class="py-lineno">161</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        (class C{X2goProxyNX3}) this originally is the session name. With X2go it </tt> </tt>
-<a name="L162"></a><tt class="py-lineno">162</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        defines the name of the NX cache directory. Best is to leave it untouched.</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L163"></a><tt class="py-lineno">163</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @type cache_type: str</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L164"></a><tt class="py-lineno">164</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @param kblayout: keyboard layout, e.g. C{us} (default), C{de}, C{fr}, ...</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L165"></a><tt class="py-lineno">165</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @type kblayout: str</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L166"></a><tt class="py-lineno">166</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @param kbtype: keyboard type, e.g. C{pc105/us} (default), C{pc105/de}, ...</tt> </tt>
-<a name="L167"></a><tt class="py-lineno">167</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @type kbtype: str</tt> </tt>

+<a name="X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT"></a><div id="X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT-def"><a name="L143"></a><tt class="py-lineno">143</tt> <a class="py-toggle" href="#" id="X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT-toggle" onclick="return toggle('X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT');">-</a><tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-keyword">class</tt> <a class="py-def-name" href="x2go.backends.terminal.stdout.X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT-class.html">X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT</a><tt class="py-op">(</tt><tt class="py-base-class">object</tt><tt class="py-op">)</tt><tt class="py-op">:</tt> </tt>

+<a name="L145"></a><tt class="py-lineno">145</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    Class for managing X2go sessions on a remote X2go server via Paramiko/SSH. </tt> </tt>
+<a name="L146"></a><tt class="py-lineno">146</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    With the L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT} class you can start new X2go sessions, resume suspended </tt> </tt>
+<a name="L147"></a><tt class="py-lineno">147</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    sessions or suspend resp. terminate currently running sessions on a </tt> </tt>
+<a name="L148"></a><tt class="py-lineno">148</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    connected X2go server.</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L149"></a><tt class="py-lineno">149</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
+<a name="L150"></a><tt class="py-lineno">150</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    When suspending or terminating sessions there are two possible ways:</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L151"></a><tt class="py-lineno">151</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
+<a name="L152"></a><tt class="py-lineno">152</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        1. Initialize an X2go session object, start a new session (or resume)</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L153"></a><tt class="py-lineno">153</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        and use the L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT.suspend()} or L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT.terminate()} method</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L154"></a><tt class="py-lineno">154</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        to suspend/terminate the current session object.</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L155"></a><tt class="py-lineno">155</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        2. Alternatively, you can pass a session name to L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT.suspend()}</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L156"></a><tt class="py-lineno">156</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        or L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT.terminate()}. If a session of this name exists on the</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L157"></a><tt class="py-lineno">157</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        X2go server the respective action will be performed on the session.</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L158"></a><tt class="py-lineno">158</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
+<a name="L159"></a><tt class="py-lineno">159</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    An L{X2goTerminalSessionSTDOUT} object uses two main data structure classes: </tt> </tt>
+<a name="L160"></a><tt class="py-lineno">160</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
+<a name="L161"></a><tt class="py-lineno">161</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        - L{X2goSessionParams}: stores all parameters that have been passed to the </tt> </tt>
+<a name="L162"></a><tt class="py-lineno">162</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        constructor method.</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L163"></a><tt class="py-lineno">163</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
+<a name="L164"></a><tt class="py-lineno">164</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        - C{X2goServerSessionInfo} backend class: when starting or resuming a session, an object of this class </tt> </tt>
+<a name="L165"></a><tt class="py-lineno">165</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        will be used to store all information retrieved from the X2go server.</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L166"></a><tt class="py-lineno">166</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring"></tt> </tt>
+<a name="L167"></a><tt class="py-lineno">167</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @param geometry: screen geometry of the X2go session. Can be either C{<width>x<height>}</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L168"></a><tt class="py-lineno">168</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">        or C{fullscreen}</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L169"></a><tt class="py-lineno">169</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @type geometry: str</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L170"></a><tt class="py-lineno">170</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @param depth: color depth in bits (common values: C{16}, C{24})</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L171"></a><tt class="py-lineno">171</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @type depth: int</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L172"></a><tt class="py-lineno">172</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @param link: network link quality (either one of C{modem}, C{isdn}, C{adsl}, C{wan} or C{lan})</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L173"></a><tt class="py-lineno">173</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @type link: str</tt> </tt>
+<a name="L174"></a><tt class="py-lineno">174</tt>  <tt class="py-line"><tt class="py-docstring">    @param pack: compression method for NX based session proxying</tt> </tt>
